scenario: Late-morning foot traffic at Potsdamer Platz: office workers and visitors cross the square in multiple directions, using open corridors around the circular installations.
Evening commuter drift: people leave nearby offices and head toward transit stops and taxi ranks, keeping to the clear edges and corridors.
Weekend shoppers and tourists slowly traverse the plaza, moving between café fronts and information boards without a single focal point.
Cloudy morning ambulation: small groups wander, some cutting across the north edge while others drift toward the southwest exits.
Light drizzle prompts brisk walking: umbrellas bob as pedestrians aim for sheltered edges and nearby stop points.
Accessibility meet-up: wheelchair users and companions move toward an accessible ramp and assistance point on the south side, then disperse to various exits.
Guided walk for visually impaired participants arrives from the northeast to a safe meeting area on the north side; helpers later escort them to edges for pickup.
Hearing-impaired community workshop wraps up near the northeast corridor; attendees move calmly toward multiple egress points.
Mobility scooter training finishes at mid-east; participants navigate out along clear lanes toward widely spaced pick-up zones.
Assisted evacuation drill: stewards guide a small group with mixed mobility southward, then to safe waiting areas at the edges.
Cohesive guided tour: a single group gathers at the north plaza and then moves together toward viewpoints around the square.
Parade rehearsal unit forms at the west corridor and advances cohesively toward the east edge waypoint.
Corporate team-building walk: the group meets at the northeast and moves as a unit to a designated south-side finish.
Film crew relocation: a compact team gathers mid-east and traverses together to a staging area on the southeast walkway.
Tourist group crossing: guide assembles travelers at the north edge and escorts them diagonally to the southwest exit in one cohesive flow.
Flash-mob dance: performers and onlookers converge on the north plaza, forming a lively circle before drifting to edges.
Street musician draws a crowd near the mid-east walkway; people cluster to watch, then peel off toward exits.
Chalk art jam on the south side: families gather to participate, later dispersing to north and west edges.
Banner drop and chanting at the north corridor: a small expressive crowd forms a ring and then diffuses across the plaza.
Pop-up dance circle by the southwest seating area; spectators gather briefly and then wander off to various corners.
Open-air market with several small stalls dotted along the perimeter; participants drift among them.
Public yoga class: mats set up near the south walkway; attendees filter in and settle.
Tech demo booths along the northeast and east edges invite passersby to participate; people approach whichever is closest.
Interactive light installation at the north side; visitors gather, try it, then wander off to other corners.
Charity fundraiser with donation points at north, east, and south; participants choose a nearby station.
Heated argument erupts near the mid-east walkway; nearby pedestrians veer away, increasing distance to safe edges.
Small scuffle breaks out near the south corridor; most bystanders avoid the area and head for exits.
Argument between cyclists escalates at the north plaza; onlookers briefly pause while others skirt around to distant sides.
Rival groups exchange shouts near the west corridor; some curious pedestrians edge closer while most detour toward safer zones.
Delivery dispute turns tense at the northeast corner; the surrounding crowd quickly avoids the hotspot.
Climate march occupies the square, converging on a small stage near the east corridor and holding signs.
Pro-democracy rally forms at the north side; arrivals stream toward the gathering while others spread to the edges for visibility.
Workers’ demonstration moves from south toward the north banner point, occupying the open lanes.
Peace vigil assembles at the southwest walkway; participants quietly converge and maintain a compact formation.
Student march aims for the northeast corridor; the crowd advances with chants and placards.
Sudden loud crack near the northeast causes alarm; people quickly flee toward all clear edges.
Electrical sparking near the east corridor triggers evacuation; pedestrians scatter to the far north and south exits.
Smoke reported by the southwest walkway; people move away from the source toward dispersed safe points.
Unidentified threat heard at the north plaza; runners bolt toward the west and south edges.
Loud crash near the southeast prompts rapid dispersal to opposite sides of the square.
Holiday crowd at noon fills the open lanes; movement is slow and compact without a single focal point.
Film premiere queue forms along the east corridor; the crowd thickens near the entry while remaining areas see slow drift.
Weekend street fair compresses people near several perimetral stalls; foot traffic remains dense and slow.
Rain shower: pedestrians cluster under edge awnings, creating pockets of high density and minimal movement.
Multiple tour groups converge at the north plaza before splitting; density around the meeting point is high and motion slow.
Transit rush: people hurry toward the east-side bus bay, choosing the nearest clear lanes.
Showtime call: attendees scramble to the south entry point, cutting across open corridors.
Flash sale announcement at the northeast pulls shoppers who speed across the plaza.
Photo-op countdown at the north plaza; participants dash in from multiple sides to make it in time.
Checkpoint sprint: runners and cyclists cut to a finish beacon at the southwest edge.
A blast is reported near the east corridor; the crowd bolts away toward distant edges and corners.
Knife fight breaks out near the southwest walkway; people flee from the hotspot toward safer, well-separated exits.
Fire flashes near the northeast; alarms spread and pedestrians evacuate quickly to opposite sides.
Vehicle collision at the north plaza escalates; bystanders sprint away, avoiding the area and heading for clear edges.
Confrontation turns riotous near the west corridor; the crowd rapidly escapes to far corners and edges.
